    a2: 'The $119 diagnostic in Midtown covers both gas and electric ovens reflecting the neighbourhood mixed building stock. For gas ranges in older Midtown buildings, the technician tests igniter draw current, checks the gas safety valve, inspects burner ports for blockages, and performs a gas leak check at all connections. Oven temperature calibration is verified. For electric ranges in newer Midtown condos, each bake and broil element is resistance-tested, the temperature sensor is checked for accuracy, and the control board is scanned for error codes. On induction ranges, each coil zone is tested for output faults. We run a full heat cycle on all types to confirm accurate temperature. You receive a written, itemized quote before any work proceeds -- no hidden fees, no obligation. If you approve the repair on the same visit, the $119 fee is waived and applied to the total. Nika serves Midtown seven days a week. Weekday evening appointments until 8pm are available for working residents. Call (437) 524-1053.',
    q3: 'What are the most common oven problems in Midtown homes?',
    a3: 'Midtown Toronto, centred on Yonge and Eglinton, contains an unusually diverse mix of housing: older apartment buildings and co-ops from the 1960s-1980s where gas ranges remain in use, and newer condo towers where electric and induction are standard per building code. In the older Midtown buildings, gas igniter failure is the most common oven repair -- the igniter weakens over years of use until it can no longer draw enough current to open the gas safety valve. Thermostat drift on older gas units is also common. In the newer Midtown condo towers, control board failures generating E and F error codes are the most frequent issue. These codes indicate failed temperature sensors, stuck relays, or board communication faults. Induction coil failure -- one zone producing no heat -- is the second most common in newer buildings. Bake element burnout is common across all electric oven types. We also see self-clean thermal fuse failures on older units throughout the neighbourhood. Nika technicians carry parts for both gas and electric models on Midtown service calls.',
    q4: 'How does same-day oven repair work in Midtown?',
    a4: 'Same-day oven repair in Midtown starts with a call to (437) 524-1053 or an online booking before noon. We cover all of Midtown including Yonge-Eglinton, Davisville, Forest Hill, Deer Park, and the surrounding streets. After booking, you receive a confirmed 2-4 hour arrival window the same day. For high-rise buildings, provide your unit number, buzzer code, and visitor parking information when booking -- our technicians navigate Midtown condo buildings routinely. The van carries both gas oven parts (igniters, thermostats, temperature sensors) and electric oven parts (bake elements, control boards, surface elements, induction coil modules). The $119 diagnostic is completed first, then a written quote is provided. Standard repairs take 60-90 minutes. All repairs include a 90-day parts and labour warranty. Evening appointments until 8pm on weekdays are available for residents with daytime scheduling constraints. Nika has served Midtown since 2017.',
    q5: 'What should I prepare before the oven technician arrives in Midtown?',
    a5: 'Before your technician arrives at your Midtown home or condo, turn the oven off and allow it to cool. For gas ranges in older Midtown buildings, leave the gas supply on for live testing. For electric glass-top or induction ranges, allow the surface to cool for at least 45 minutes. Remove all racks and pans from the oven interior and clear the stovetop. Note the exact symptoms: for gas ovens, does it click but not light, or light and then cut out? For electric, which specific element or zone stopped working? Write down any error codes exactly as shown on the display. Find the model number on the sticker inside the oven door frame. For Midtown condo buildings, have your visitor parking code, unit number, and buzzer information ready to include in your booking notes. Many Midtown buildings require advance elevator booking for service calls -- check with your concierge if your building has this requirement, as arranging it in advance avoids delays on the day of service.',
